<emphasis effect="bold">How did a fracturing of the liberal consensus shape politics and culture between 1968 and 1980?</emphasis><newline/>
<emphasis effect="bold">Option C: Explain the causes and effects of continuing policy debates about the role of the federal government during the period 1968â€“1980.</emphasis><newline/>
Through this inquiry, students will evaluate primary and secondary sources to explain the factors that contributed to political and cultural change from 1968â€“1980. Ultimately, students will use the primary and secondary sources in this chapter to practice constructing an essay, in AP Long Essay Question format, demonstrating their skills in explaining historical causation. Students should be evaluated using the <link url="https://apstudents.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/2019-05/ap-us-history-course-and-exam-description.pdf">AP Rubric</link>. Assess studentsâ€™ progress in understanding the compelling question for this chapter by assigning the <link document="m83596">Unit 7 Essay Activity</link>.</entry>
